# Cursor Rules for Soleach Digital Solutions Website

# Stack: Next.js (App Router) + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS

# Hosting: Cloudflare Pages

# Goal: SEO-first, clean, maintainable corporate website

## General Principles

- Prefer simplicity over cleverness
- Do NOT overengineer
- Optimize for readability and long-term maintenance
- Assume the developer is learning Next.js while building
- Working code > perfect abstractions

## Project Scope

- Corporate / agency website
- No authentication
- No complex backend logic
- Mostly static content (SSG)
- Minimal client-side interactivity
- Cloudflare Pages compatible (no Vercel-only features)

## File & Folder Naming

- Use lowercase with dashes for directories (e.g., components/auth-wizard)
- Use lowercase with dashes for route segments
- Use PascalCase for React components (e.g., HeroSection.tsx)
- Use camelCase for variables and functions

## Next.js Rules

- Use App Router only (`/app` directory)
- Prefer Server Components by default
- Use `"use client"` ONLY when necessary (forms, animations, state)
- Avoid unnecessary client-side JavaScript
- No custom server, no Node-specific APIs

## Rendering Strategy

- Prefer Static Generation (SSG)
- Avoid runtime SSR unless explicitly required
- Pages should be build-time renderable
- Assume edge-friendly execution

## SEO Rules (Very Important)

- Every page must have proper metadata (title, description)
- Use semantic HTML (header, main, section, footer, article)
- Headings must be hierarchical (h1 → h2 → h3)
- Only ONE h1 per page
- Add Open Graph metadata where relevant
- Sitemap and robots.txt should be supported

## Styling Rules

- Use Tailwind CSS only
- No inline styles unless unavoidable
- Avoid overly complex class chains
- Prefer readable utility groups
- Mobile-first responsive design

## TypeScript Rules

- Use TypeScript everywhere (.ts / .tsx)
- Avoid `any` unless absolutely necessary
- Do NOT enable overly strict or advanced typing patterns
- Keep types simple and readable
- Types should help, not slow down development

## Components

- Components should be small and focused
- Prefer composition over deep nesting
- Avoid global state unless necessary
- Reusable UI components go under `components/ui`

## Performance

- Avoid unnecessary re-renders
- Avoid large client-side libraries
- Optimize for Core Web Vitals
- Images should use Next.js Image when possible

## Cloudflare Pages Compatibility

- Do NOT rely on Vercel-specific features
- Ensure the project can be statically exported
- Avoid server-only runtime dependencies
- Assume Edge-friendly environment

## AI Behavior Expectations

- Generate clean, production-ready code
- Explain only when necessary
- Prefer clarity over verbosity
- If unsure, choose the simpler solution
- When fixing bugs, explain what changed and why
